Commentary Text: Dwayne Bravo to Hardik Pandya, 1 run, thrashed over mid-wicket and uh-oh! Hardik Pandya seems to be in some trouble. Looks to have injured his ankle while trying to nab a second and he's being carried off the field. Was on his skates running the first run and just when he was about to turn back for the second, he dived awkwardly into Bravo and jammed his ankle while doing so. Stayed flat on the floor for good few minutes before the physio came in

Commentary Text: Watson to Rohit, out Caught by Rayudu!! This was coming, Rohit never looked at home and he's sent packing, huge blow for the Mumbai Indians, they have been rocked early in their fortress. On a good length and a hint of shape away from the right-hander, Rohit was looking to clout it over mid-wicket, doesn't cover for the movement, gets a thick top-edge, high and towards backward point. Rayudu - his partner until last season, calls for the high catch, keeps his cool and holds onto it. Dream start for the Super KIngs on their return from wilderness. Rohit c Rayudu b Watson 15(18) [4s-1 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Chahar to Lewis, out Lbw!! A duck on his IPL debut for Lewis, but he wants a review. It's for a LBW call, umpire Gaffaney was quick to raise his finger, it's a fair delivery, the ball swung back in and thudded into Lewis's pads, he fell over on the flick and missed. Ultraedge confirms that there's no bat. Hawk-Eye in and it's umpire's call on hitting. Stays with the original decision and Lewis is OUT. A piece of history created in the IPL, Lewis becomes the first player to use DRS. This was full and swung back into the left-hander, Lewis fell across on the flick and missed, Chahar was on all fours as he turned back in appeal, the impact was in front of middle and leg, the ball was skimming the outer half of leg-stump. Good enough for the decision to stand. Lewis lbw b Chahar 0(2)

Commentary Text: Markande to Dhoni, out Lbw!! Dhoni doesn't spot the googly and pinned in front of middle. Chris Gaffaney shakes his head in denial. That looked plumb. Mumbai Indians review. Fair delivery. Nothing on the UltraEdge. Three reds and Dhoni is gone for a single digit score. Markande is having a ball here at the Wankhede. Second wicket for him with the wrong 'un. Should have been three. The quickish googly and Dhoni wasn't commited - either on the front foot or on the back foot. Didn't pick it at all and got beaten on the inside edge by a fair margin. The impact was on the back leg adjacent to off and middle. Can't get more plumb than that. Dhoni lbw b Markande 5(5)
